summary: Jin - He finds you passed out When Jin comes into the apartment you both live in, he’s whistling cheerily as he thinks of you....
body:
Jin - He finds you passed out

When Jin comes into the apartment you both live in, he’s whistling cheerily as he thinks of you. It’s Friday, and also the start of a two-week break from his schedule. He had wanted to surprise you, so he called you boss a few hours ago to book the time off for you too, and you have no idea! He can’t want to see your face when he tells you.

He calls out after he’s shut the door and put his shoes and coat away. It’s not unusual for you to be hidden up somewhere, napping after a hard day or finishing up some last bits of work in the study, so Jin doesn’t worry when you don’t respond. It means that he can make a start on dinner while you do whatever it is that you’re doing. He knows better than to wake you from a nap!

“Oh my… jagiya, what have you done?” Jin gasps, upon seeing his worst fear in the kitchen in front of him. You’re collapsed in an ungraceful heap, arms slightly outstretched like you’d passed out while trying to get a jar down. Jin hurries to kneel down next to you, rolling you onto your side in a vague attempt at the recovery position. He doesn’t remember it well and his hands are shaking so badly, but he tries his best.

Through his panic, Jin manages to assess the situation. You’re unconscious but your breathing is completely normal. From the look of it, you’re exhausted. Jin doesn’t blame you - you’ve been working so hard, but luckily you have the next two weeks to relax and rest up with your beloved boyfriend, who is doing his best to care for you in this vulnerable state.

Jin slowly changes you out of your work clothes and redresses you in your sweatpants and one of his shirts (which was far more difficult than he thought it would be) and then carries you over to the couch, where he lays you down on his chest and holds you close. At this point, Jin’s definitely sure that you’re just sleeping off your exhaustion, since you keep twitching your nose and whining like you do at night. You’ve moved a little to cling onto his shirt loosely, and the two of you are wrapped up with each other under the fluffiest blanket Jin could find. One of his hands rests on the small of your back as the other flicks something onto the TV, before opening up an eating app to order some take away. When you wake up, it’d be nice for Jin to have some food ready and waiting for you,

“Jin?” You ask sleepily, as he’s setting the bag of food down. When the doorbell had rung, he hadn’t wanted to put you down, so he simply took you with him, holding you to him like a baby while he awkwardly took the food and shut the door with his foot, “What happened?”

“I’m not really sure. I came home and you’d collapsed. I was so worried,” Jin tells you, voice soft with concern, “But it’s okay, you’re okay. We have some food here, and I’ve booked you some time off from work. We both have two weeks off, and I’ve been thinking about taking you out of the country for a while,” Jin continues, although well aware that you might not quite take all of it in. You do manage to realise that he’s been sweet though, no matter how tired you are. You kiss his neck lazily and hold tighter to your boyfriend, so thankful that he’s patient and caring with you.

body:
pairing: bts x reader
fandom: bts
warnings: language
genre: crack ; fluff

a/n: hey love! thank you so much! so glad you like my stuff! hope you enjoy this one as well!

ask box | masterlist | fandoms | faq | multifandom reader blog

kim seokjin

You had decided to go work out together today, but maybe that had been a bad idea.

Because Jin’s usually so confident self, was having problems with certain equipment that his girlfriend managed to do with ease.

When he was lifting some weights and his arms were about to give in, you came to his rescue, smiling down at him, “Need some help with that?”

“Nope. I’m managing,” he said through gritted teeth.

“You sure, hun? I can..-”

“No, I’m fine. Go do your thing, Jagi,” he tried to smile, but it somehow looked awfully painful. But the second you let go again and had turned around, was the second he gave up, almost being crushed by the weights, “No, no, no! Come back! I wasn’t serious!”

min yoongi

You were out with the boys, since they were shooting another Run episode in an amusement park. During their break, Yoongi had sat down with a water bottle next to you and had been desperately trying to open it for five minutes.

Eventually, you just had enough of his angry grunts and insults and snatched it out of his hands, opening it up with ease and handing him the open bottle.

“I uh.. I did the groundwork,” he nodded.

“If that’s what you want to tell yourself, babe,” you shrugged.

Yeah. That’s exactly what he wanted to tell himself.

jung hoseok

“Hobi, you won’t fall into the water, if you step onto the stones.”

“But they’re wet! What if I slip?”

Hey, pro-tip? Never go on a hike and NOT follow the trail, when your boyfriend is scared of pretty much everything.

“Fine. You leave me no other choice.”

You crossed the small river again and turned around, giving him a piggyback ride, without informing him beforehand.

“What are you doing?” he started panicking, but before you knew it, he pretty much clang onto you like a second skin, “Don’t slip, don’t slip, don’t slip,” he muttered under his breath like a mantra. 

Of course you didn’t slip, because it wasn’t as bad as he thought it was. As soon as you had crossed the river, you let him back down and he cleared his throat.

“So uh.. mind if we keep this to ourselves?” you only laughed and walked away, “Wait, is that a yes? Jagi! Wait for me!”

kim namjoon

“Do you really want to do this, Joon? Are you a hundred percent sure that you’re willing?”

“C'mon, baby,” he grinned at you, “A man’s gotta have some fun from time to time.”

“Oh, I agree. But see,” you took one step towards him, so that your boobs were touching his chest and looked into his eyes, “I think you’ve got the wrong girlfriend for that game.”

“We’ll see about that.”

All you wanted was that goddamn last cookie and he thought he’d have his fun and hold it as high in the air as he could, just because he thought he could tease you like that.

But since he was standing right in front of the bed, you easily tackled him onto it and snatched the cookie out of his hand like it was nothing, happily munching on it while you were straddling him a moment later.

“Hey! That wasn’t fair, you..-”

“You stole my cookie. Everything is fair when you do that,” you said, your mouth filled to the brim, but a big smile on your face nevertheless.

park jimin

He had really planned on letting you sleep in for once. He wanted to wake up his five month old daughter, change her diapers, feed her and go for a stroll, all before you would even wake up. With him being gone so often, he felt like it was his duty to do all of this whenever he could.

But while your daughter was becoming impatient in her high chair and started whining when her father didn’t bring her food as soon as she was sat, Jimin had trouble of even opening up the stupid container with her baby food.

After he saw the quivering lip of his daughter, he knew he had no other choice but to quickly run into the bedroom and gently shake you awake.

“(Y/N)? Can you open this up for me?”

“Huh?” you turned on your back and slowly sat up, still being half asleep, your eyes not really even open, but just doing what he asked you to, to whatever he put into your hands.

“Thank you,” he grinned as soon as it was open and kissed your forehead, “Sleep some more.”

Good thing he was married to someone like you, or he’d be lost in the world of parenthood.

kim taehyung

“I’m not sure this is a good idea, Tae..”

“What.. scared?” he wiggled his eyebrows.

“Yeah. For your ego.”

For some reason, Taehyung had thought it was a fun idea to do some arm wrestling. But when you actually did it, you didn’t give him three seconds of a chance, before you had already won and he just stared at his failed arm in disbelief, then up at you with a pout.

“I warned you,” you shrugged, an apologetic smile on your face.

“Can you make it up to me?”

And maybe, just maybe, from the way he was looking at you with this glint in his eyes, you could have sworn that this had been his plan all along.

Sneaky bastard.

jeon jeongguk

It actually just started out as playful sparring, you know, like couples occasionally did. But with both Jeongguk and you being competitive as fuck, you ended up taking it a little more serious than most couples would have and what began as child’s play, ended up in both of you trying to dominate the other.

Usually, Jeongguk was very confident in his abilities and his strength.

But with you it was different.

He tried telling himself that he went easy on you because you were his girlfriend and because he didn’t want to hurt you, but the truth was simply that he had no chance against you, when you finally straddled him and pinned down his arms above his head, grinning down happily at him.

“I won.”

“Are you su..-” he wanted to turn you two around again, but he really had no chance. So he plopped back down again and nodded, “Fine. You won.”

You giggled and leaned down to press a soft kiss against his mouth.
